               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾāmra Māryām “Miracles of Mary” (fols. 2ra-117ra)&#xD;
I-1) Maṣḥafa śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah and hymns (fols. 2ra-6vb)&#xD;
I-2) ʾƎsaggǝd laki wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki ... “I worship Thee ...” (fols. 6vb-7vb)&#xD;
I-3) Introductory exhortation (fols. 7vb-9ra)&#xD;
I-4) Taʾāmra Māryām: 100 miracles (9rb-117ra)&#xD;
I-5) ʾAkkonu bǝʾǝsi ... “Does not the man ...” (distributed among the miracles of Mary, fols. 14va-49va)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-1 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ḫoḫǝta mǝśrāq ... “Salutation to you, Threshold of the East ...” (<locus target="#5va">5va-</locus>vb) <!-- = LIT4714Salamlaki (MV 2017-09-07) --></note>
                     <note>- Walādita ʾamlāk Māryām ʾǝnbala säbsab wa-rukabe ... “Mary, Godbearing without marriage and intercourse ...” (last strophe of the hymn ʾAkkonu bǝʾǝsi ... “Does not the man ...”) (<locus target="#5vb">5vb</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- Sǝbḥāt laki Māryām ba-ḫʷǝlqʷa malāʾǝkt za-ʾaryām ... “Glory to you, Mary, as numerous as the angels of ʾAryam ...” (<locus target="#5vb">5vb</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus kahāli ... “O my Lady Mary, Mother of Jesus the Almighty ...” (<locus from="5vb" to="6ra">5vb-6ra</locus>) (cp. ChRep n<locus target="#373">373</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma bǝrhān ... “Salutation to you, o my Lady Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ...” (<locus target="#6ra">6ra-</locus>vb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>All miracles of Mary (Text I-4) are numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
